    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Harvey</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 132.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 28, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 262, of the 28th of February,
                    has been received, and has been read with much interest. The course of events
                    subsequent to its date serves to confirm the correctness of the political
                    intelligence which you have communicated.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
